{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/domestic-violence-abuse/goals-outcome-measures/goals/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"3b1d2b4f-e678-5bc0-b63c-804c2d05baeb","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 0fb87081-6c46-490c-b788-a8e200a8f27f --><h2>Goals</h2><!-- end field 0fb87081-6c46-490c-b788-a8e200a8f27f -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item db61bc53-792f-4d40-95f2-a8e200a8f27f --><!-- begin field 224ba675-961a-4a1a-8e71-a8e200a8f27f --><p>To support primary healthcare professionals to:</p><ul><li>Recognize the signs of possible domestic violence and abuse.</li><li>Facilitate disclosure of domestic violence and abuse sensitively and safely.</li><li>Assess the person to ascertain whether they and/or any children are in immediate danger, to inform a safe plan of management and referrals to specialist support services.</li><li>Assess the person for any physical injuries or mental health conditions and to manage these appropriately.</li><li>Support children who are affected by domestic violence and abuse.</li><li>Manage people who disclose that they are perpetrating domestic violence and abuse.</li><li>Provide information on support groups.</li><li>Document domestic violence and abuse and manage the person's notes safely.</li><li>Share information appropriately.</li></ul><!-- end field 224ba675-961a-4a1a-8e71-a8e200a8f27f --><!-- end item db61bc53-792f-4d40-95f2-a8e200a8f27f -->","topic":{"id":"b977b12b-9567-5da6-abb1-760920456e01","topicId":"505227d2-9718-489c-9aac-a8e200a8e8f1","topicName":"Domestic violence and abuse","slug":"domestic-violence-abuse","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2018","chapters":[{"id":"223f1d71-49ce-5ed9-b847-6237e6ea5a85","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bb0b0eb5-c67f-51e0-9580-8ace3ed80c0f","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","sub